From: lavenly <135024283+lavenly@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 05:20:13 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] interfaces: camera: relax metadata buffer size check in
 sDataCbTimestamp

Older legacy camera HALs (such as Exynos 3475) utilize a 20-byte metadata buffer rather than the standard 8-byte Android VideoNativeHandleMetadata. The strict equality check in sDataCbTimestamp (`size == sizeof(VideoNativeHandleMetadata)`) causes these custom buffers to be silently rejected by the HIDL transport layer, preventing the native file descriptors from being correctly unmarshaled and passed to cameraserver.

This patch changes the strict equality check to a `>=` check, allowing the custom metadata struct to pass validation and restoring video recording capabilities for legacy devices relying on hardware-specific metadata sizes.

Generated with Antigravity (https://antigravity.google) using Gemini 3.1 Pro (High)

Change-Id: I45affb5018b667ceaa4371b3d8daee4712bdaeed
Signed-off-by: lavenly <135024283+lavenly@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 camera/device/1.0-legacy/CameraDevice.cpp | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/camera/device/1.0-legacy/CameraDevice.cpp b/camera/device/1.0-legacy/CameraDevice.cpp
index f324e45..9825f93 100644
--- a/camera/device/1.0-legacy/CameraDevice.cpp
+++ b/camera/device/1.0-legacy/CameraDevice.cpp
@@ -508,7 +508,7 @@ void CameraDevice::sDataCbTimestamp(nsecs_t timestamp, int32_t msg_type,
 
     native_handle_t* handle = nullptr;
     if (object->mMetadataMode) {
-        if (mem->mBufSize == sizeof(VideoNativeHandleMetadata)) {
+        if (mem->mBufSize >= sizeof(VideoNativeHandleMetadata)) {
             VideoNativeHandleMetadata* md = (VideoNativeHandleMetadata*)
                     ((uint8_t*) mem->mHidlHeapMemData + index * mem->mBufSize);
             if (md->eType == kMetadataBufferTypeNativeHandleSource) {
